Package controllers

Class AddAppointmentController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controllers.AddAppointmentController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable
    public class AddAppointmentController
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    This class is the controller of AddAppointmentMenu.fxml. The class displays two TableViews and various buttons to create a new Appointment.
    Since:
    2021-12-13

      • onActionCancelButton

        public void onActionCancelButton​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        This method is called when the "Cancel" button is clicked. This method sends the user to SchedulingMenu.fxml without adding the Appointment.
        Parameters:
        event - high-level event used to set the Stage

      • onActionSaveButton

        public void onActionSaveButton​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        This method is called when the "Save Appointment" button is clicked. This method checks that all necessary values have been entered by the user and that they are valid. The method also check the time slot selected to confirm neither the contact or customer selected are already booked.

        RUNTIME ERROR: Should the Insert into the database fail, an error message will appear.

        Parameters:
        event - high-level event used to set the Stage
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - required by the FXMLLoader.load() function
